-- Colombian Stock Movers: ETB, Ecopetrol, Bancolombia Were Active
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-05-09T20:33:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/colombian-stock-movers-etb-ecopetrol-bancolombia-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  decreased 0.1 percent to 15,169.65, while
the  Colcap Index (COLCAP)  fell 0.2 percent to 1,793.63.  Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota SA  (ETB CB), the
phone company serving  Colombia ’s capital, fell 0.8 percent to
502 pesos. Shareholders approved ETB’s proposal to take on as
much as $600 million in debt, according to a regulatory filing.  Bancolombia SA (BCOLO)  , Colombia’s biggest lender,
gained 1.4 percent to 30,360 pesos. Bancolombia will report an
increase in first-quarter profit to 448.3 billion pesos ($253.6
million), according to the average estimate of four analysts in
a Bloomberg survey. Bancolombia will report its results today
after the market is closed, according to an e-mailed statement.  Oil producers dropped in line with crude as U.S. supplies
rose to the highest level in almost 22 years. The price for
crude oil for June delivery slipped for the sixth day, the
longest downward run since July 2010.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest  oil company ,
fell 0.5 percent to 5,620 pesos.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMG)  ,
a Calgary-based oil company that operates in the Andean region,
fell 0.4 percent to 24,280 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
